.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-5-20::.
City: edinburgh, hannover, boston, rome
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, ship, skateboard, snowmobile
1. the person traveling to hannover is somewhere to the left of the person driving the ship##5
2. the person traveling to edinburgh is on the right of the person driving the snowmobile##1
3. the person driving the skateboard is in an odd position##4
4. the person driving the car is somewhere to the right of the person driving the ship##5
5. the person traveling to hannover is somewhere to the left of the person driving the snowmobile##5
6. the person traveling to edinburgh is between the person traveling to rome and the person driving the car##2

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |     2      |     3     |     4      |
| City        | hannover     | rome | edinburgh | boston |
| Transport   | skateboard | snowmobile | ship      | car        |

 